  "summary": "Luigi Mazzoni is shot twice and falls forward. Nearby, Bianca hears what she believes to be a gunshot but dismisses the sound and returns to sleep.\n\nLater, Miss Knight arrives breathless to inform Miss Marple that the Italian butler, Giuseppe, was shot the previous night. Miss Knight attributes the violence to \"American hooligans.\" Miss Marple suspects that Giuseppe was killed because he was attempting to blackmail someone, noting that he had traveled to London the day before his death.\n\nMiss Marple pulls Shirley aside to discuss the matter privately. Shirley reveals that her friend Gladys, a restaurant worker and acquaintance of Giuseppe, had intended to ask him about something \"odd\" she had observed. Shirley also mentions a rumor that Mr. Rad's secretary suffered a heart attack and may be dead, but the conversation remains focused on Giuseppe.\n\nShirley explains that Gladys worked at the party involving the death of Mrs. Baskerville. According to Shirley, Gladys observed something strange regarding Mrs. Baskerville and a cocktail; specifically, Gladys claimed that Mrs. Baskerville intentionally spilled a cocktail on her own skirt to ruin it. Shirley finds this detail ridiculous and suspects Gladys may be withholding the true nature of what she saw. Miss Marple expresses concern that Gladys did not report her observations to the police, suggesting that the significance of the event may be misunderstood or that crucial facts are missing.",
